// Leetcode Problem:
// appraoch:- first, iterate through each row of given grid(matrix).
// while iterating each row of given matrix, use of set to encounter value in each row meanwhile check
// if current iterated value of a row is a number which is already present in the set then 
// return false from there only as the row contain duplicate. likewise, iterate through each column
// of given grid(matrix) and while iterating column again use of set to encounter value in each column
//  meanwhile check if current iterated value of a column is a number which is already present in the
//  set then return false from there only as the column contain duplicate.
// There are nine 3x3 sub-matrix in a 9x9 Sudoku board.
// Iterate over each sub-matrix by moving in steps of 3 (i.e., i += 3 and j += 3).
// Use a Set to track the numbers encountered in the current sub-matrix.
// For each cell(single box) in the 3x3 sub-matrix,  check if the number is already in the Set.
// If the number is in the Set, the sub-matrix contains duplicates, so return false.
// If the number is not in the Set, add it to the Set.
// The time complexity remains O(1), because we are iterating over a fixed number of cells (81) which
// we have 9 rows and 9 columns.
// The space complexity is also O(1), as we are using a fixed amount of additional space (has set)
// (3 arrays of 9 blocks).

var isValidSudoku = function (board) {
    let row = board.length;
    let col = board[0].length;

    //Check for rows that it contain any duplicate or not
    for (let i = 0; i < row; i++) {
        let set = new Set();
        let count = 0;
        for (let j = 0; j < col; j++) {
            if (board[i][j] != ".") {
                if (set.has(board[i][j])) {
                    return false;
                } else {
                    set.add(board[i][j])
                }
            }
        }
    }

//Check for columns that it contain any duplicate or not
for (let j = 0; j < col; j++) {
    let set = new Set();
    for (let i = 0; i < row; i++) {
        if (board[i][j] != ".") {
            if (set.has(board[i][j])) {
                return false;
            } else {
                set.add(board[i][j])
            }
        }
    }
}


// Check for each 3x3 sub-matrix that it contain any duplicate or not
for (let i = 0; i < row; i += 3) {
    for (let j = 0; j < col; j += 3) {
        let set = new Set();
        for (let k = i; k < i+3; k++) {
            for (let l = j; l < j+3; l++) {
                let value = board[k][l];
                if (value != ".") {
                    if (set.has(value)) {
                        return false;
                    }
                    set.add(value);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}


return true;
};